    <string name="privacy_policy_body">Usage Access Permission\nThis app uses Usage Access only to detect when apps selected by the user are opened, so the app can show the lock screen. Usage data is processed locally on the device and is not uploaded, sold, shared, or used for advertising.\n\nDisplay Over Other Apps\nThis app uses Display Over Other Apps only to show the lock screen over protected apps.\n\nForeground Service\nThis app uses a foreground service to keep App Lock protection active while enabled by the user.\n\nPremium Tools\nPremium cleanup tools such as duplicate finder, large file finder, and storage analyzer process vault files locally on the device. No photos, videos, documents, notes, file names, or analysis results are uploaded or shared.\n\nPrivate Notes and Private Documents are stored locally in encrypted form. The app does not upload or share this content.\n\nHidden and locked albums are privacy features controlled by the user and stored locally on the device.</string>

